g.text: The metrics system has two components -- a collection service and a query service.
The collection service receives messages from the app. The messages contain a value that represents the response time for each request the app receives.
The query service can return aggregate values of metrics sent to the collection service.
- The collection service should accept messages in the format: (key,value)
- If an instance of the collection service is not available:
+ It should not affect the client
+ It should not affect the collection service's ability to respond to requests
+It should not affect the query service's ability to respond to requests
- Users should be able to have data collected
- Users should be able to query results
Avg, min, max, med respose/load times
GET hostname, key(pageId), stat_type (min, max, ..), date, hour
+ Query API should respond in milliseconds (with caching).
+ Handle thousands to millions of events per second across instances
+ Always should respond to requests, even if some components are down or behind.
+ Flink updates aggregates when late events arrive
> This is acceptable because metrics don’t usually require perfect real-time accuracy.
Design a metrics system that can be used for collecting response times for a hypothetical app.
- Exposes a JSON endpoint that returns aggregates of metrics by hour for a particular instance of an app.
+ Hours are non-overlapping. (i.e. tumbling windows, not sliding windows)
- The format of the JSON endpoint URI should be:
* stat_type is one of the following aggregate functions: average, min, max, median
- Users should be able to interact with the endpoint using curl
